</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="111" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
Open growth form; leaves linear or ensiform with dark coloration at base and peltate branched hairs; inflorescences bearing many flowers; flowers with a long perianth tube (1.3-3.1 mm); staminate flowers with long filaments (3.8-8.6 mm), anthers basifixed, immobile; pistillate flowers with long outer tepals (1.5-6.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.9-1.6 mm); ovary trilocular, intermediate length (2.1-4.8 mm); fruit globose or obpyriform, with few to many seeds per fruit (1-22); seeds ellipsoid or ovoid, small and narrow (1.3-2.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.1-1.1 mm); funicle short, truncate, with well-developed mucilaginous funicular hairs that adhere to the seed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="111" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
Species published under 
<taxonomicName authority="Skottsberg, 1934" authorityName="Birch" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Collospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Collospermum" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Collospermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be transferred as 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Astelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has nomenclatural priority. Synapomorphies recognized for the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Skottsberg, 1934" authorityName="Birch" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Collospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Collospermum" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Collospermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Skottsberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B28" refString="Skottsberg, C, 1934. Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander. Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar 14 (2): 1 - 128" title="Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander." volume="14" year="1934">Skottsberg 1934</bibRefCitation>
) remain valid for 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Collospermum) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="hastatum" subGenus="Collospermum" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Collospermum</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
